 - see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"40 g butter"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"sea salt, to taste (optional - see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"ground black pepper, to taste (optional)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"extra virgin olive oil, to serve"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"micro herbs, to serve"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"lemon, cut into cheeks, to serve"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","1673 kJ \/ 398.3 kcal","41.6 g","25.4 g","13 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["<b>Baby's serve<b>: for a younger baby, omit salt and blend together fish and green mash, adding as much liquid (water or baby's milk) as needed to achieve desired consistency (you may need none). For an older baby, keep the blended consistency more textured or simply serve as is, cut up as needed.","<b>Toddler's serve<b>: omit or reduce salt and serve as is, cut up as needed.","Ask your fish monger to pin bone your fish (or purchase fish that's already boneless). The cooking times will vary depending on the thickness of fish fillets used. If you can't fit all of your fish onto the Varoma tray, you can put some into the Varoma dish. Feel free to adjust the quantity of fish according to the appetites of your family.","The mash has a natural sweetness thanks to the sweet potato - I use a white sweet potato so that the mash is a prettier green colour than if purple or orange was used."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","50m","4 portions"]}